~/.config/waybar/style.css

This CSS file uses the official Dracula color palette, providing a clean and consistent look. The styling is minimalist, with subtle rounded corners and spacing to make each module stand out without being cluttered.
CSS

/* Dracula Color Palette */
@define-color background #282a36;
@define-color foreground #f8f8f2;
@define-color current_line #44475a;
@define-color comment #6272a4;
@define-color cyan #8be9fd;
@define-color green #50fa7b;
@define-color orange #ffb86c;
@define-color pink #ff79c6;
@define-color purple #bd93f9;
@define-color red #ff5555;
@define-color yellow #f1fa8c;

/* General Waybar styles */
* {
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    font-family: "JetBrainsMono Nerd Font"; /* Use a Nerd Font for icons */
    font-size: 13px;
    min-height: 0;
}

window#waybar {
    background-color: @background;
    color: @foreground;
    transition-property: background-color;
    transition-duration: .5s;
}

/* Module styles */
.modules-left,
.modules-center,
.modules-right {
    background-color: @current_line;
    margin: 4px;
    padding: 0 8px;
    border-radius: 12px;
}

#workspaces button {
    background-color: transparent;
    color: @foreground;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0 5px;
}

#workspaces button:hover {
    background-color: @comment;
}

#workspaces button.active {
    background-color: @purple;
    color: @background;
}

#window {
    font-weight: bold;
}

#clock {
    color: @green;
}

#cpu {
    color: @cyan;
}

#memory {
    color: @orange;
}

#pulseaudio {
    color: @pink;
}

#pulseaudio.muted {
    color: @comment;
}

#tray {
    color: @foreground;
}

How to use this configuration:

    Create the directories: If you don't already have them, create the waybar config directory:
    mkdir -p ~/.config/waybar/

    Save the files:

        Save the JSON content into ~/.config/waybar/config.

        Save the CSS content into ~/.config/waybar/style.css.

    Install dependencies:

        waybar itself.

        A Nerd Font like ttf-jetbrains-mono-nerd (replace "JetBrainsMono Nerd Font" in the CSS with your font's name).

        Optional: htop for the CPU/Memory on-click action.

        Optional: pavucontrol for the audio on-click action.

    Reload Waybar: You can add waybar & to your Hyprland config (~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf) to start it automatically. To reload it after making changes, you can simply run pkill waybar and then waybar & in your terminal.

